<p>Dr. Hu An has reviewed and offered advisory on the following SCP objects.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;View&nbsp;List&nbsp;of&nbsp;Reviewed&nbsp;SCPs</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;List&nbsp;of&nbsp;Reviewed&nbsp;SCPs</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<table class="wiki-content-table">
<tr>
<th>SCP No.</th>
<th>Codename</th>
<th>Commentary</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2617">SCP-2617</a></td>
<td>Winter Battalion Command</td>
<td>It touches on a decent stretch of history, from the start of the Russian Empire to the USSR during WWII and how people of respective eras interact with said anomaly.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2955">SCP-2955</a></td>
<td>Every Wandering Golden City of the Caesars</td>
<td>It explores the idea of the &quot;lost city of gold&quot; and turns it into a cat-and-mouse game for both the Foundation and the many explorers before them.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2159">SCP-2159</a></td>
<td>Head-&quot;Kanon&quot;</td>
<td>It is a commentary of sorts: While we always consider headcanons of a franchise, these headcanons are but unified by that common point between all of them. Sometimes, even the creators of the franchise might take influence from the fanbase and incorporate into their end-product (ascended fanon).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2698">SCP-2698</a></td>
<td>O Great One Communing Human via Computer</td>
<td>It started out as a fridge logic take on tentacle erotica, which evolved into a homage into Lovecraftian works and grew an absurdist tone.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2312">SCP-2312</a></td>
<td>A Petty King</td>
<td>I am primarily proud of incorporating the aspect of security clearance to justify a short article from an in-universe perspective.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2248">SCP-2248</a></td>
<td>Temple of Luna Primogenita</td>
<td>It incorporates trivial bits of history and myth, enough to get people to imagine the events of the past.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2833">SCP-2833</a></td>
<td>Lineage of Vaski</td>
<td>My first attempt on Sarkicist SCPs, it leads itself to world-building of a setting paved by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/metaphysician" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1698079); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1698079&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869514" alt="Metaphysician" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1698079)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/metaphysician" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1698079); return false;">Metaphysician</a></span>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2430">SCP-2430</a></td>
<td>Immortal Hitler Clone</td>
<td>Despite the nickname of &quot;Immortal Hitler Clone&quot;, it is not all of the above in how one would expect normally.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2511">SCP-2511</a></td>
<td>Kappa Population Distribution: More in Mongolia than anywhere else</td>
<td>While there is SCP-140, SCP-1237 or SCP-2140 that shift reality on a whim, we don't really see the results. This SCP here <em>may</em> or <em>may not</em> be the aftermath of this manner of anomalies. Either that or God is a bunch of novelists with weird sense of humour.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2372">SCP-2372</a></td>
<td>Soulmates</td>
<td>In many cultures, they believe that the soul is not singular and has many sub-components. Even in your intimate moments, you are not alone and this article butts into the intimate moments of a person.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2752">SCP-2752</a></td>
<td>Junk Male</td>
<td>This is my experimental attempt at weirdness-oriented SCPs.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2457">SCP-2457</a></td>
<td>母を見たい (&quot;<em>haha o mitai</em>&quot;)</td>
<td>This brings out the investigative aspects of the Foundation's employees.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2478">SCP-2478</a></td>
<td>Ordinary Japanese People</td>
<td>If one can become part of the in-group, does it matter if you become monstrous (literally and figuratively)?</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2953">SCP-2953</a></td>
<td>Polymorphism-Inducing Rocks</td>
<td>While anomalies can be used for political manipulation, why bother when there is good old-fashion military might? Also, there is more to <a href="/scp-953">SCP-953</a> than the generic monster everyone made her to be.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2748">SCP-2748</a></td>
<td>Driving Roadkill from Xiangxi</td>
<td>A prompt from reddit was the inspiration for this, and it became the vehicle for an idea I did not find time or means to get about.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-392">SCP-392</a></td>
<td>A Plant Now Found in Site-103, and Formerly Found in the Households of Nobility</td>
<td>An expansion on Daevite culture, and how other cultures use this piece of decontextualised culture.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2720">SCP-2720</a></td>
<td>Penguin Honeymoon Suite</td>
<td>A semi-homage to <em>Love Live Sunshine!</em>, something that I grew fond of. The other half is a brief consideration about Foundation fronts that would rather do their &quot;fake&quot; job for real.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2781">SCP-2781</a></td>
<td>Bodhisattva of the High Seas</td>
<td>Between the previous duty of the Foundation and newfound duty of a bodhisattva, the Middle Way prevails.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/wrong-proposal">SCP-001 (Wrong Proposal)</a></td>
<td>The Consensus</td>
<td>My magnum opus and entry for History Contest 2017. It is a summation of my headcanon and the things I like about the Foundation-verse manifested on the site for posterity. A.K.A. runner-up entry for the History Contest 2017.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2596">SCP-2596</a></td>
<td>A Big Ship-load</td>
<td>I wanted to focus on the Horizon Initiative and explore a more subtle side to their not-really-elaborated anti-cult movements.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-3434">SCP-3434</a></td>
<td>&#8230;And We'd Rather Remain in the Darkness</td>
<td>My entry for SCP-3000 Contest. While some get to live in the light, what happens in the darkness?</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2857">SCP-2857</a></td>
<td>Dr. Ji Fan, PhD SOCA</td>
<td>A homage to Singapore, chicken rice, and a world where the only thing worth learning is the art of cooking (with everything available via Google).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-3609">SCP-3609</a></td>
<td>Hati Hróðvitnisson</td>
<td>An exercise in writing interviews. The base anomaly might be mundane, but that's not the main dish. Not at all.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-3047">SCP-3047</a></td>
<td>To Be Drowned By A Train</td>
<td>Having gotten out of a recent writer's block, it took a statement from a Japanese light novel, and have it remade in my imagery.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-3257">SCP-3257</a></td>
<td>A Priest in a Suitcase at Timbuktu</td>
<td>My submission to <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-1703757">LordStonefish's challenge</a>. Using selected terms, I combined it with my childhood musings of a human packed inside luggage and realised the potential it can have with Fifthism.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-3341">SCP-3341</a></td>
<td>Arabian Nasnas a.k.a. Somalian Hungruf</td>
<td>My experiment with elaborating an obscure mythical creature, to the point of building several cultures around it and real-world events.</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
</div>
</div>
