<tr>
<th>Tale</th>
<th>Commentary</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/how-173-got-to-site-19">How 173 Got to Site-19</a></td>
<td>It tackles 3 aspects: A lampshade to attempts of 173-orientated Tales a la <a href="/revised-entry">Revised Entry</a>, an answer to why 173's description begins with &quot;Moved to Site-19&#160;1993&quot;, and the implications of a &quot;true&quot; Foundation operating on a multiversal scale that effectively reduces the value of entire realities into that of D-class personnel.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/project-morpheus">Project Morpheus</a></td>
<td>It develops on the &quot;true&quot; multiversal Foundation concept that I pioneered, and hints on the World Tree concept (which will be the postulate of my argument). In that sense, it is a good starting point.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/database-error">Database error?</a></td>
<td>SCP-2140 may be short for a Thaumiel, but it can let loose a whole can of worms. This may well be the first of these worms.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/santa-s-new-home">Santa's New Home</a></td>
<td>A strange interpretation of Santa in the SCP multiverse, mixed with a Christmas tale.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-the-anime-part-4-gears-iceberg-clef-kondraki-rights-ligh">SCP the Anime, part 4 (Gears/Iceberg, Clef/Kondraki, Rights/Light, Kain, monkey!Bright)</a></td>
<td>It manages to be an outlet for me to throw down quite a number of my headcanon in writing, and allow me to do the anime-SCP Foundation crossover that I struggle to accomplish. Also, I get to smash the 4th wall.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/indwelling-of-bright">Indwelling of Bright</a></td>
<td>The Doctors of the Church canon was among the first canons I read, and I am fascinated by the different takes on common Foundation tropes (e.g. the D-class). It is only an absolute shame for them to be left buried in the flood of new stuff.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/etymology-of-die-glocke">Etymology of die Glocke</a></td>
<td>Modified from my entry for 2016 X-mas Art Exchange, I took MacLeod's character of Otto Weber and made him a character. He may have worked for the Nazis, but not all Nazis have to be painted with the same stroke.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/dai-to-a">Dai-tō-a</a></td>
<td>A Tale kinda focusing on IJAMEA, and companion piece to SCP-2752's ending.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/exhibitionist-fantasising">Exhibitionist Fantasising</a></td>
<td>My tribute for <a href="/173-festival">173fest</a>. This mirrors the daydreaming of a person to overcome their woes.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/commentary-on-selected-items-in-the-seimei-gallery">Commentary on Selected Items in the Seimei Gallery</a></td>
<td>There needs to be more content about IJAMEA, but I have trouble over where to start. And thus, I began from the beginning.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/heroic-spirit-alexei-belitrov">Heroic Spirit Alexei Belitrov</a></td>
<td>My first Project Crossover Tale, which combines the fate franchise with SCP-2273 (an SCP which I regard as the contemporary Able).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/the-picture-of-an-unian">The Picture of an Unian</a></td>
<td>My entry for 2017 X-mas Art Exchange. I decided to deliver fanservice to taylor_itkin, who has used his likeness in one of his SCP.</td>
</tr>
